    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "List all integers between $-6$ and $4$."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Which integers satisfy both conditions: greater than $-10$ and less than $-2$?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Find the opposite and absolute value of each:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$-17$ **(b)** $23$ **(c)** $0$ **(d)** $-(-8)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Compare using $<$, $>$, or $=$:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$-12 \\quad \\rule{0.8cm}{0.4pt} \\quad -5$",
        "$|-9| \\quad \\rule{0.8cm}{0.4pt} \\quad |9|$",
        "$-(-4) \\quad \\rule{0.8cm}{0.4pt} \\quad 4$",
        "$-7 \\quad \\rule{0.8cm}{0.4pt} \\quad 0$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(-15) + (-8)$ **(b)** $23 + (-35)$ \n **(c)** $(-42) + 42$ **(d)** $(-7) + 15 + (-3)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Find the sum: $(-12) + 8 + (-5) + 12 + (-8) + 5$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use properties to simplify: $(-37) + 15 + 37 + (-15)$"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$8 - 20$ **(b)** $(-6) - 9$ \n **(c)** $15 - (-7)$ **(d)** $(-11) - (-25)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Simplify: $10 - 25 - (-8) + (-3) - 12$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Find the difference between $-18$ and $47$."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(-9) \\times 7$ **(b)** $(-12) \\times (-5)$ \n **(c)** $8 \\times (-11)$ **(d)** $(-4) \\times (-3) \\times (-2)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(-1)^8$ **(b)** $(-2)^4$ \n **(c)** $(-3)^3$ **(d)** $-2^4$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(-72) \\div 9$ **(b)** $84 \\div (-7)$ \n **(c)** $(-100) \\div (-25)$ **(d)** $0 \\div (-13)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Evaluate if possible:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\displaystyle \\frac{-45}{-9}$ **(b)** $\\displaystyle \\frac{0}{-8}$ \n **(c)** $\\displaystyle \\frac{-15}{0}$ **(d)** $\\displaystyle \\frac{-48}{6}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(-4) + 3 \\times (-5)$ \n **(b)** $(-6)^2 - 40$ \n **(c)** $\\displaystyle \\frac{(-3) \\times 8}{-6}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Evaluate: $|{-8}| + (-3)^2 - 5 \\times (-2)$"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If $a = -4$ and $b = 6$, evaluate:"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$a + b$ **(b)** $a - b$ \n **(c)** $ab$ **(d)** $\\displaystyle \\frac{b}{a}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The temperature was $-8$°C at midnight. By noon, it rose 15°C. \nThen by midnight, it fell 12°C. What was the final temperature?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "A submarine at $-120$ meters rises 45 meters, then dives 80 meters. \nWhat is its final depth?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "An investor loses \\$250 per month for 8 months, then gains \\$75 per month \nfor 4 months. What is the net change in the investment?"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Jacob worked 7 years for Laban to marry Rachel, then was tricked and \nhad to work 7 more years (Genesis 29). If we represent years of \nindentured labor as negative time, write an expression for Jacob's \ntotal \"debt\" of time. What is $(-7) + (-7)$?"
    }
  ]
}